            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:400;color:#1E293B;margin-bottom:16px;line-height:1.6;text-align:justify;">Dear Investor,</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:14px;">Taranis Market Sentiment ended the month of April 2026 with a net performance of +34.1%.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:14px;">April proved to be an exceptional month for global equities. The Iran-U.S. conflict continued to dominate headlines, with the Strait of Hormuz severely disrupted and Brent crude pushing above $110 per barrel. Yet global markets looked decisively through the turbulence: the S&P 500 and Nasdaq reached all-time highs, driven by a powerful rotation back into AI and semiconductor names. Our long/short strategy delivered an outstanding monthly performance (+34.1%). Both our direct equity holdings and futures positions contributed meaningfully, with equities continuing to represent approximately a third of our overall exposure.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:700;color:#1E293B;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:14px;">Our semiconductor allocation (16% of the fund) was among the strongest contributors of the month, led by SK Hynix surging to an all-time high on April 28 as its Q1 2026 operating profit rose five-fold on record HBM demand from AI clients. South Korean and Taiwanese markets surged +38% and +26% respectively. Creotech completed the long-anticipated spin-off of its quantum division (ex-date April 23), a structural catalyst we had been positioned for, and OHB maintained its momentum as European defence-space sovereignty attracts growing sovereign capital commitments.</div>

            <div style="font-family:'Aktiv Grotesk','aktiv-grotesk','Helvetica Neue','Arial',sans-serif;font-size:13px;font-weight:300;color:#334155;line-height:1.75;text-align:justify;margin-bottom:28px;">Our short book faced pressure as the broad rally lifted names previously weakened by AI disruption narratives. Fair Isaac (FICO) rebounded sharply after reporting Q2 2026 revenue of $691.7 million (+39% year-on-year), reversing its prior month derating. We continue to identify structural short opportunities in legacy and mid-tier software as enterprise budgets accelerate their rotation toward AI-native solutions. Notable short-side headwinds included Figma and CoStar, which recovered ground amid the risk-on rally.</div>

